cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.SE, cs.AI, cs.PL 

The paper proposes a novel approach for modeling programming languages using deep neural networks, specifically a tree-based convolutional neural network (TBCNN). This falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning (ML), which are covered by cs.CL and cs.LG respectively. Additionally, the paper focuses on the processing of programming languages, which falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE). The use of deep neural networks also falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper specifically mentions abstract syntax trees (ASTs), which are a key component of programming languages and fall under the category of programming languages (cs.PL).
